{
  "stem": "2522.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The prospect of baptism, while deportations take place, take a very simple view.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That you do that because you have to do it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The alternative is, is, is too bad to contemplate.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what of a-- what of a apprehension my mother would have had, and particularly my father's parents-- who did not get baptized, by the way-- that was quickly brushed away in the rush to do all the proper things and fill out all the forms.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You must understand, in order to get a white card and to get baptized, it involved an enormous amount of legal rigmarole and procedural rigmarole.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I, I think that-- I remember it as a fairly smooth procedure.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We, we had to actually go to, to catechism schools and, and study the Christian religion and understand what it says.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we actually had to pass an examination.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, you must understand that part of the heritage of that whole culture is extreme dominance of the state over private lives.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And so if you follow those procedures you are certified as having done the right thing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, she had to.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, but she went through the motions because that was the right thing to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, many other Jews got baptized too.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And let me just say that in April and May of 1942, you would have signed your blood to the devil.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, you know, if the devil himself would have come and asked you for a [INAUDIBLE], you would have done it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did not have to wear a star.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "See, baptism was a way of preserving your life.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But all of those other laws still applied to you as a Jew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, this was a very convenient arrangement.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
